&#8220;Comrade Jonas has served both as Deputy Minister and MP with absolute distinction and dedication,&#8221; the office of the ANC Chief Whip said in a statement.Office of the ANC CW confirms the resignation of former Deputy Finance Minister &amp; ANC MP Cde Mcebisi Jonas as an MP effective 31 March 2017.&mdash; ANC Parliament (@ANCParliament) April 6, 2017Jonas was removed from his position along with Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan last week during a late night Cabinet reshuffle by President Jacob Zuma.The dismissal of Gordhan and Jonas has been criticised by unions, civil society groups and the opposition, and has revived pressure on Zuma to quit.The president appointed Malusia Gigaba as the new finance minister and Sfiso Buthelezi as his deputy.This is a developing story.&nbsp;